# Live Weather & Risk Assessment Integration

This module will add real-time environmental context to the AI prediction engine, allowing the app to recommend harvesting a crop based on imminent weather risks.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend (FastAPI - [backend/main.py](file:///c:/Users/katik/OneDrive/Desktop/EVERYTHING/harvest/perishable-farming-platform/backend/main.py))
New tools and APIs:
- Add `httpx` and `python-dotenv` to [requirements.txt](file:///c:/Users/katik/OneDrive/Desktop/EVERYTHING/harvest/perishable-farming-platform/backend/requirements.txt).
- Set up a `.env` file for OpenWeatherMap API Keys.
- Create a new endpoint `POST /weather-risk` that takes `latitude` and `longitude`.
- Implements logic to call OpenWeatherMap One Call API or Current Weather API.
- Generates a "Harvest Risk Score" based on simple heuristics (e.g., if rain > 10mm, risk = High).

### Frontend (React Components)
New tools and APIs:
- Uses browser geolocation `navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition()`.
- Updates [src/components/Dashboard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/katik/OneDrive/Desktop/EVERYTHING/harvest/perishable-farming-platform/frontend/src/components/Dashboard.jsx) to fetch and pass coordinates to the backend when the app loads.
- Creates `src/components/WeatherWidget.jsx` to display current weather status, a 5-day simplified forecast, and the computed Harvest Risk Score.

## Verification Plan
### Automated testing
- Not applicable for this hackathon sprint.

### Manual Verification
- Ask user to approve browser location prompt.
- Verify Weather Widget properly loads and correctly calculates a "Harvest Risk Score".
